ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div class="pl-2 pt-1 pb-2"><div class="font-ui bg-bg-000 rounded-2xl rounded-t-3xl overflow-hidden border-border-300 border -mx-1 mb-4 transition-colors focus-within:border-accent-200/50 focus-within:shadow-md"><div class="flex flex-col"><div class="overflow-y-auto max-h-[400px]"><div style="opacity: 1; filter: blur(0px); transform: none;"><textarea placeholder="Write your message..." class="px-5 pt-4 pb-4 w-full resize-none bg-transparent border-none text-sm text-text-100 placeholder:text-text-500 !outline-none !ring-0" style="field-sizing: content; min-height: 200px;">Every large-scale system starts with a single commit.

Today I began building GridSense — a Real-Time Industrial Energy Intelligence Platform designed for European industrial operators.

🔍 The Problem:
European energy grids are becoming increasingly unstable due to renewable energy unpredictability. German industries alone lose €4+ billion annually from poor energy management.

⚡ What GridSense will do:
→ Fetch live EU electricity data via ENTSO-E API
→ Predict next 24hr energy consumption using ML
→ Detect anomalies and flag unusual spikes in real-time
→ Visualize CO₂ intensity and weather correlations

🛠️ Day 1 Progress:
✅ Project architecture designed
✅ GitHub repository initialized
✅ FastAPI backend running locally
✅ ENTSO-E API access requested

Tech Stack: Python • FastAPI • Next.js • Prophet • XGBoost • WebSockets

This project sits at the intersection of Industry 4.0, ML forecasting, and real-time systems — exactly where I want to be.

Following along? I'll be posting daily updates. 🚀

#GridSense #Python #FastAPI #MachineLearning #EnergyTech #Industry40 #RealTimeData #OpenToWork</textarea></div></div><div class="flex items-center justify-end gap-2 px-2 py-2"><div class="flex items-center h-8 bg-bg-000 rounded-lg border-0.5 border-border-300 shadow-sm overflow-hidden"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
