ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Kamal, pehle ek baat — <strong>tumhara previous post bura nahi tha!</strong> Bilkul solid tha. Bug fix describe karna, lesson share karna — yeh sab bahut genuine aur relatable hai. Employers yeh dekhte hain.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Bas kuch cheezein aur polish kar sakte hain:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Hook line aur strong honi chahiye — pehli line pe log ruk jaayein</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Thoda storytelling add karo</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Screenshot attach karo — visual proof bahut important hai</li>
</ul>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Screenshot mein kya attach karo:</strong></p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Yeh 2 cheezein screenshot lo aur post mein lagao:</p>
<ol class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-decimal flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Browser mein</strong> <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs</code> — GridSense API ka Swagger UI</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><strong>Browser mein</strong> <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">http://127.0.0.1:8000</code> — <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">{"message": "GridSense API is running!"}</code> wala page</li>
</ol></div></div><div class="pl-2 pt-1 pb-2"><div class="font-ui bg-bg-000 rounded-2xl rounded-t-3xl overflow-hidden border-border-300 border -mx-1 mb-4 transition-colors focus-within:border-accent-200/50 focus-within:shadow-md"><div class="flex flex-col"><div class="overflow-y-auto max-h-[400px]"><div style="opacity: 1; filter: blur(0px); transform: none;"><textarea placeholder="Write your message..." class="px-5 pt-4 pb-4 w-full resize-none bg-transparent border-none text-sm text-text-100 placeholder:text-text-500 !outline-none !ring-0" style="field-sizing: content; min-height: 200px;">Day 1 — GridSense Project Started.

I just ran my first FastAPI server locally and got this response:

{ "message": "GridSense API is running!" }

Small line. Big feeling.

Here's what I'm building:
GridSense — a Real-Time Industrial Energy Intelligence Platform for European industrial operators.

The problem it solves:
German industries lose €4+ billion every year because of poor energy management. No affordable real-time prediction tool exists for factory operators. GridSense will change that.

What it will do:
→ Live EU electricity data via ENTSO-E API
→ 24hr energy consumption forecasting using ML
→ Real-time anomaly detection
→ CO₂ intensity tracking

Day 1 progress:
✔ Project architecture finalized
✔ GitHub repo initialized
✔ FastAPI backend running
✔ ENTSO-E API access requested

Bug I fixed today:
.env file was created with wrong encoding by PowerShell.
UnicodeDecodeError crashed the server.
Fix — recreated the file using Python with utf-8 encoding.

Lesson: Always verify file encoding when working cross-platform.

Tech Stack: Python • FastAPI • Next.js • Prophet • XGBoost • WebSockets

Daily updates coming. Follow along. 🚀

GitHub: [your GitHub link here]

#GridSense #Python #FastAPI #EnergyTech #Industry40 #MachineLearning #100DaysOfCode #OpenToWork</textarea></div></div><div class="flex items-center justify-end gap-2 px-2 py-2"><div class="flex items-center h-8 bg-bg-000 rounded-lg border-0.5 border-border-300 shadow-sm overflow-hidden"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
