<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">git add .</code> — sab files ko "staging area" mein daala, matlab Git ko bataya ki in files ko track karo</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">git commit</code> — ek snapshot liya — jaise photo kheenchi project ki us moment ki</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2"><code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">git push</code> — woh snapshot GitHub pe upload kar diya</li>
</ul>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<h2 class="text-text-100 mt-3 -mb-1 text-[1.125rem] font-bold">3. Python Virtual Environment Banaya</h2>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]"><strong>Kya hai virtual environment?</strong> — Ek isolated bubble. Socho aise — tumhare computer pe Python installed hai. Agar tum directly uspe packages install karo toh sab projects ek hi jagah share karenge. Agar Project A ko <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">requests==2.28</code> chahiye aur Project B ko <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">requests==2.33</code> chahiye — conflict ho jaayega.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Virtual environment har project ka apna alag Python environment banata hai.</p>
