ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Samajh gaya! Bilkul usi format mein banata hun — clean, simple, no overdone emojis.</p></div></div><div class="pl-2 pt-1 pb-2"><div class="font-ui bg-bg-000 rounded-2xl rounded-t-3xl overflow-hidden border-border-300 border -mx-1 mb-4 transition-colors focus-within:border-accent-200/50 focus-within:shadow-md"><div class="flex flex-col"><div class="overflow-y-auto max-h-[400px]"><div style="opacity: 1; filter: blur(0px); transform: none;"><textarea placeholder="Write your message..." class="px-5 pt-4 pb-4 w-full resize-none bg-transparent border-none text-sm text-text-100 placeholder:text-text-500 !outline-none !ring-0" style="field-sizing: content; min-height: 200px;">Day 1 : GridSense — Project Started.

Building a Real-Time Industrial Energy Intelligence Platform for European industrial operators.

The Problem:
- European energy grids are unstable due to renewable energy unpredictability
- German industries lose €4+ billion annually from poor energy management
- No affordable real-time prediction tool exists for factory operators

What GridSense will do:
- Fetch live EU electricity data via ENTSO-E API
- Predict next 24hr energy consumption using ML
- Detect anomalies and flag unusual spikes
- Track CO2 intensity across European grid zones
- Correlate energy usage with live weather data

Day 1 Progress:
- GitHub repo initialized
- FastAPI backend running
- ENTSO-E API access approved
- Live energy data fetching from Germany, France, Spain, Poland
- Weather data integration complete

Bug fixed today:
- .env file created with wrong encoding by PowerShell
- UnicodeDecodeError crashed the server
- Fix: recreated file using Python with utf-8 encoding

Tech Stack:
- Backend: Python, FastAPI
- ML: Prophet, XGBoost
- Frontend: Next.js (coming soon)
- Deployment: Vercel + Render (coming soon)

GitHub: https://github.com/kamal-lochan-sahu/gridsense

Project-2 Status: In Progress

#Python #FastAPI #MachineLearning #EnergyTech #Industry40 #100DaysOfCode #OpenToWork</textarea></div></div><div class="flex items-center justify-end gap-2 px-2 py-2"><div class="flex items-center h-8 bg-bg-000 rounded-lg border-0.5 border-border-300 shadow-sm overflow-hidden"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
