ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Bilkul! Day 2 post banata hun — CropSense wale clean format mein.</p></div></div><div class="pl-2 pt-1 pb-2"><div class="font-ui bg-bg-000 rounded-2xl rounded-t-3xl overflow-hidden border-border-300 border -mx-1 mb-4 transition-colors focus-within:border-accent-200/50 focus-within:shadow-md"><div class="flex flex-col"><div class="overflow-y-auto max-h-[400px]"><div style="opacity: 1; filter: blur(0px); transform: none;"><textarea placeholder="Write your message..." class="px-5 pt-4 pb-4 w-full resize-none bg-transparent border-none text-sm text-text-100 placeholder:text-text-500 !outline-none !ring-0" style="field-sizing: content; min-height: 200px;">Day 2 : GridSense — Live Energy Data Pipeline Complete.

Today I built the full data pipeline that fetches and parses real-time electricity data from European power grids.

What I built:
- ENTSO-E XML data fetcher for 4 European countries
- XML parser to convert raw energy data into clean format
- Weather data integration via Open-Meteo API
- REST API endpoints to serve live data

Live data fetched today:
- Germany: 50,044 MW average load
- France, Spain, Poland: all fetched successfully
- Berlin weather: 6.0°C, Wind 10.7 km/h

API Endpoints built:
- GET /energy/germany — live German electricity load
- GET /energy — all 4 countries at once
- GET /weather/berlin — live Berlin weather
- GET /weather — all cities at once

Bug fixed today:
- raw_xml was truncated to 500 characters
- XML parser was failing with unclosed token error
- Fix: removed the slice, passing full XML response

Lesson: Never truncate data before parsing. Always work with the complete response.

Tech Stack:
- Backend: Python, FastAPI
- Data: ENTSO-E API, Open-Meteo API
- Parsing: Python xml.etree.ElementTree

GitHub: https://github.com/kamal-lochan-sahu/gridsense

Project-2 Status: In Progress

#Python #FastAPI #EnergyTech #Industry40 #MachineLearning #100DaysOfCode #OpenToWork</textarea></div></div><div class="flex items-center justify-end gap-2 px-2 py-2"><div class="flex items-center h-8 bg-bg-000 rounded-lg border-0.5 border-border-300 shadow-sm overflow-hidden"><div class="w-fit" data-state="closed"><button class="inline-flex
