ansparent [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.standard-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pl-2 [&amp;_.progressive-markdown_:is(p,blockquote,ul,ol,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6)]:pr-8"><div><div class="standard-markdown grid-cols-1 grid [&amp;_&gt;_*]:min-w-0 gap-3 standard-markdown"><p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Haan bilkul! Yeh already ek web app hai — live internet pe chal raha hai. Koi bhi duniya mein <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">https://gridsense-eight.vercel.app</code> khol ke use kar sakta hai.</p>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Agar tumhara matlab hai <strong>aur features add karna</strong> — toh haan, bahut kuch add kar sakte hain jaise:</p>
<ul class="[li_&amp;]:mb-0 [li_&amp;]:mt-1 [li_&amp;]:gap-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ul]:pb-1 [&amp;:not(:last-child)_ol]:pb-1 list-disc flex flex-col gap-1 pl-8 mb-3">
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">User login system</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Alert notifications</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">ML forecasting (Prophet + XGBoost)</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">Mobile responsive design</li>
<li class="whitespace-normal break-words pl-2">WebSocket real-time updates</li>
</ul>
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Abhi pehle <strong>README.md</strong> likhte hain — phir discuss karenge ki aage kya add karna hai.</p>
<hr class="border-border-200 border-t-0.5 my-3 mx-1.5">
<p class="font-claude-response-body break-words whitespace-normal leading-[1.7]">Root folder mein <code class="bg-text-200/5 border border-0.5 border-border-300 text-danger-000 whitespace-pre-wrap rounded-[0.4rem] px-1 py-px text-[0.9rem]">README.md</code> kholo:</p>
